# Kubernetes — Zero to Hero

A structured learning path + command reference, in the same style as the Docker guide.
Kubernetes assumes you're already comfortable with Docker (images, containers, networks, volumes) —
K8s is the layer that runs and manages many containers across many machines.

---

## Stage 0: Why Kubernetes exists (30 min read)

Docker Compose is great for one machine. But in production you need:
- Multiple servers (nodes) running containers, not just one
- Automatic restart if a container crashes
- Automatic scaling up/down based on load
- Rolling updates with zero downtime
- Service discovery and load balancing across many replicas

**Kubernetes (K8s)** is a container orchestrator that solves all of this. Mental model:
you describe the **desired state** ("I want 3 replicas of this app running, exposed on port 80"),
and Kubernetes continuously works to make reality match that description.

