## Stage 4: Configuration — ConfigMaps & Secrets (Week 3)

Never hardcode config or credentials into images — inject them at runtime, same principle as Docker Compose env vars.

```bash
kubectl create configmap app-config --from-literal=DB_HOST=postgres-service
kubectl create secret generic app-secret --from-literal=DB_PASSWORD=supersecret
kubectl get configmaps
kubectl get secrets
kubectl describe configmap app-config
```

```yaml
# ConfigMap YAML
apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: app-config
data:
  DB_HOST: postgres-service
  DB_PORT: "5432"
```

```yaml
# Secret YAML (values must be base64-encoded)
apiVersion: v1
kind: Secret
metadata:
  name: app-secret
type: Opaque
data:
  DB_PASSWORD: c3VwZXJzZWNyZXQ=
```

Consuming them in a Deployment:
```yaml
env:
  - name: DB_HOST
    valueFrom:
      configMapKeyRef:
        name: app-config
        key: DB_HOST
  - name: DB_PASSWORD
    valueFrom:
      secretKeyRef:
        name: app-secret
        key: DB_PASSWORD
# or inject ALL keys at once:
envFrom:
  - configMapRef:
      name: app-config
  - secretRef:
      name: app-secret
```

