## Docker vs Kubernetes — how the concepts map

| Docker Compose | Kubernetes |
|---|---|
| `docker-compose.yml` service | `Deployment` |
| `depends_on` | Init containers / readiness probes |
| Compose network | `Service` + cluster DNS |
| `docker compose up --scale app=3` | `kubectl scale` / `replicas` field |
| Named volume | `PersistentVolumeClaim` |
| `.env` file | `ConfigMap` / `Secret` |
| `docker compose logs` | `kubectl logs` |
| Single host | Multi-node cluster |

Once you're solid here, the natural next steps are a managed cloud cluster (EKS, GKE, AKS)
and Helm chart authoring for real deployments.
